      description:
        'Born in Zagreb, capital of Croatia. After finishing the School of\nApplied Art and Design, start to work as a graphic designer and\nillustrator. 1995th became a member of Croatian Association of\nApplied Arts and participates in numerous exhibitions at home\nand abroad. 1998th he became a member of the Croatian Society\nof Independent Artists ( HZSU ).\nSince 1988, engaged in graffiti writing (nick name 2Fast),\none of the founders of the Croatian graffiti scene. Take part\non many domestic and international exhibitions and jams.\nConstantly looking for new shapes, moves and techniques,\nexploring media and materials. Last years combine street\ngraffiti into three-dimensional objects, grounded in street\nart through use of its characteristic iconography (arrows,\nnumbers and letters) physically depart the two-dimensional\nsurface by penetrating into space and are seen suspended in\nthe motion of curvature and rotation, forming unusual and\ninnovative dimension of graffiti art.\n‘2Fast belongs to the small group of graffiti-art population who did\nnot channel its youthful frustrations and potential into quick and\nfrivolous vandalisation of the public property, but rather finished\nthe School of Applied Art and Design and started working as a\ndesigner at the age of 18. In that sense, he ended up on the ‘other\nside of the fence’ and adopted the way of thinking of academically\neducated artists, such as Keith Haring or Jean-Marie Basquiat,\nknown for finding inspiration in the raw creative energy of graffiti art\namateurs and adopting the aesthetic forms and stylistic\nelements of the genre’, stated dr. sc. Darko Bekić in his foreword to\nhis latest solo exhibition exhibition.',
