      description:
        'Rodrigo Vargas is a multidisciplinary artist and freelance curator based in London\nand Barcelona. He has a bachelor’s degree in Mixed Media Fine Art from Central\nSaint Martins and has exhibited in a variety of online and offline spaces, such as\nAmbika P3, Tate Modern (Exchanges Program), 508 Kings Road Gallery, and Tecla\nSala.\n“My practice is a response to the artistic shock moving from Bogotá to London\nproduced in me. During my early years, I was exposed to the beauty and\ntimelessness of the visual arts, within offline spaces. I was a museum child, and I\nexperimented throughout my teens with painting and sculptural mediums. I believed\nit to be the epitome of creativity.\nOnce I moved to London, I realized the capabilities of the digital medium for creative\nexpression. I started experimenting with various software to create compositions to\nbe enjoyed as artwork exclusively in the digital sphere. Since then, I’ve been creating\nart under different pseudonyms and avatars, in the hopes of detaching my physical\nbeing from my digital presence, and to challenge the notion of the “celebrity artist”. I\nconsider my art to fall under the canon of contemporary art, with specific\ncategorizations of digital art, and net art.\nIn conjunction to this, I’ve curated a series of hybrid shows exploring the\ninterrelations of the digital medium and the commercial physical art world. In this I’ve\nhad the opportunity to collaborate with various NFT platforms as a curator and\nconsultant.\nI hope my series offers a short view into the creative capacities of a visual artist with\ndigital tools. Thank you for offering me a platform to showcase my work”.',
